Charge abilities:
– Summons two ankhegs
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: 2 turns

Weight: 0~
@45988 = ~Club~
@45989 = ~Club +1~
@45990 = ~Most clubs are stout, hardwood sticks, narrow at the grip and wider at the end. This simple weapon has been used since people first began using tools. Anyone can find a good stout piece of wood and swing it; hence the club's widespread use.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d6 (crushing)
Speed Factor: 4
Proficiency Type: Club
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 5 Strength

Weight: 3~
@45991 = ~From chair legs to felled trees, clubs are the universal weapons of everyone from tavern brawlers to hill giants. A little extra weight, maybe a spike or two, and a little enchantment never hurt. Which is to say, it always hurts.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1
Damage: 1d6+1 (crushing)
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Club
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 5 Strength

